http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Project-expo/article14016334.ece

Over 70 projects were on display at the Post-Graduate Group Project Exhibition 2016 organised by the M.S. Ramaiah University of Applied Sciences, Bengaluru, on Saturday. Computer Science and Engineering students showcased the Micro Air vehicle Surveillance System.Students from faculties of Engineering, Art and Design, Management and Commerce, Science and Humanities, Pharmacy, Dental Sciences, Hospital Management and Catering Technology showcased their projects. C. Shekar, Registrar and CFO of M.S. Ramaiah University of Applied Sciences, said, “True learning can only be completed if one student can transfer academic learning into product and services of relevance to the society that will make life more comfortable,” the release stated.